title: Print, "Portrait of Olivier de Clisson (1336-1407)", 1710–15
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Bust-length portrait in three-quarter view to the right.  The duke wears a beret and a coat with a fur collar. Portrait in oval frame standing on a pedestal, in front of which are a lion and a panther fighting.  Inscribed on the frame: "Tiré du Cabinet de Mr. le Comte de Rieux."

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Portrait of Olivier de Clisson (1336-1407)", 1710–15.
1710–15. Engraving on white laid paper. Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt. 1931-94-155.
